@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{vulpea-extras.el} extends the @samp{vulpea} package, a helper library for note-taking with Org Roam. Org Roam excels at linking and retrieving notes, but it does not automatically track which notes contain actionable items. This package bridges that gap by:

@itemize
@item
Detecting whether an Org Roam note qualifies as a ``project'' based on its content---TODO items, scheduled headings, deadlines, or anniversaries (@ref{Project detection}).
@item
Automatically tagging files with a @samp{"project"} tag when they meet the criteria, and removing the tag when they no longer do (@ref{Updating the project tag}).
@item
Dynamically updating @code{org-agenda-files} before each agenda invocation to include project files and recently modified notes, ensuring your agenda always reflects the current state of your knowledge base (@ref{Updating agenda files}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{paths} and @samp{vulpea}, and integrates with @samp{org-roam} and @samp{org-roam-extras.el}.

