@node Excluding directories
@section Excluding directories

@vindex vulpea-extras-excluded-directories
The user option @code{vulpea-extras-excluded-directories} specifies a list of directory paths whose contents should be excluded from project detection. Any Org file located within one of these directories or their subdirectories will be ignored by @code{vulpea-extras-project-p}, meaning it will never receive the @samp{"project"} tag automatically. The default value contains two directories defined via the @samp{paths} package. You might want to add directories that contain reference material or archival notes that should not appear in your agenda.

The type is a list of directory paths (@code{(repeat directory)}).

@node Excluding files
@section Excluding files

@vindex vulpea-extras-excluded-files
The user option @code{vulpea-extras-excluded-files} specifies individual file paths to exclude from project detection. This is useful when a specific file contains TODO items or deadlines but should not be treated as a project for agenda purposes. The default value is an empty list.

The type is a list of file paths (@code{(repeat file)}).

