@node Project detection
@section Project detection

@findex vulpea-extras-project-p
The function @code{vulpea-extras-project-p} determines whether the current buffer qualifies as a project. It returns non-@code{nil} if the buffer is in @code{org-mode}, is not in an excluded directory or file (@ref{Excluding directories}, @ref{Excluding files}), and contains at least one headline that satisfies any of the following conditions:

@itemize
@item
It is a TODO item (its @code{:todo-type} is @code{todo}) and it is not archived.
@item
It is not done and has a @code{SCHEDULED} or @code{DEADLINE} property, and it is not archived.
@end itemize

The function respects tag inheritance when checking for the @samp{ARCHIVE} tag. Completed tasks are deliberately excluded so that files containing only finished work are not flagged as active projects.

@findex vulpea-extras-anniversary-p
The function @code{vulpea-extras-anniversary-p} returns non-@code{nil} if the current Org buffer contains an anniversary expression (@samp{%%(org-anniversary ...)}). Files with anniversaries are treated as projects for tagging purposes, ensuring that recurring personal dates appear in the agenda.

@findex vulpea-extras-buffer-p
The function @code{vulpea-extras-buffer-p} returns non-@code{nil} if the current buffer's file is located within @code{org-roam-directory}. This is used as a guard to ensure that project-detection logic runs only on Org Roam files.

@node Updating the project tag
@section Updating the project tag

@findex vulpea-extras-project-update-tag
The function @code{vulpea-extras-project-update-tag} inspects the current buffer and adds the @samp{"project"} tag if the buffer qualifies as a project (via @code{vulpea-extras-project-p} or @code{vulpea-extras-anniversary-p}), or removes it if the buffer no longer qualifies. It uses @code{vulpea-buffer-tags-set} to modify the tags and only writes changes when the tag set has actually changed, avoiding unnecessary file modifications.

This function is designed to be added to a hook such as @code{before-save-hook} for Org Roam files. It includes guards against running in the minibuffer or when the buffer is in an inconsistent state (checked via @code{track-changes-inconsistent-state-p} when available).

@node Updating agenda files
@section Updating agenda files

@findex vulpea-extras-agenda-files-update
The function @code{vulpea-extras-agenda-files-update} dynamically rebuilds @code{org-agenda-files} by combining three sources:

@enumerate
@item
The current value of @code{org-agenda-files}.
@item
All files tagged with @samp{"project"} in the Org Roam database (queried via @code{vulpea-extras-project-files}).
@item
Recently modified Org Roam files (retrieved via @code{org-roam-extras-recent} from @samp{org-roam-extras.el}, limited to the last 2 days and 500 files).
@end enumerate

After merging these lists and removing duplicates, it subtracts any files listed in @code{org-extras-agenda-files-excluded}. This function is installed as @samp{:before} advice on @code{org-agenda}, so the agenda file list is always fresh when you open the agenda.

@findex vulpea-extras-project-files
The function @code{vulpea-extras-project-files} queries the Org Roam database for all files that contain a node tagged with @samp{"project"}. It returns a deduplicated list of file paths. This is the function that connects the automatic tagging system (@ref{Updating the project tag}) to the agenda file list.

@findex vulpea-extras-file-in-excluded-directory-p
The function @code{vulpea-extras-file-in-excluded-directory-p} checks whether a given file resides in one of the directories listed in @code{vulpea-extras-excluded-directories} (@ref{Excluding directories}). It is used internally by @code{vulpea-extras-project-p} to filter out files that should not be considered for project status.

